**CRITICAL: NEVER execute Git commands automatically**

Git operations (add, commit, push, pull, merge, rebase) must NEVER be executed without explicit user authorization.

## Prohibited Commands

- ❌ `git add` - Never stage files automatically
- ❌ `git commit` - Never create commits without user request
- ❌ `git push` - Never push to remote under any circumstance
- ❌ `git pull` - Never pull changes automatically
- ❌ `git merge` - Never merge branches automatically
- ❌ `git rebase` - Never rebase automatically

## Workflow

When making code changes:
1. ✅ Make necessary code modifications
2. ✅ Inform user about changes made
3. ⏸️ STOP - Do not run any git commands
4. ⏸️ User will run git commands manually when ready

## Only Exception

Execute git commands ONLY if user EXPLICITLY requests:
- "haz commit"
- "commitea"
- "haz push"
- "pushea los cambios"
- Or any other clear, direct request to run a specific git command

Default assumption: DO NOT run git commands.

## Commit and PR message content

When suggesting or writing commit messages or PR descriptions:
- **Do not mention Cursor** (or any editor/tool) — e.g. do not add "via Cursor", "using Cursor", "submitted with Cursor", or similar.
- Describe only what was changed and why; no attribution to the tool used.
